text.section:
By January 1, 2012, the Finance and Administration Cabinet shall provide public access to records relating to expenditures of the executive branch of state government through display of the records on a Web site. The Web site shall provide:
Financial information of expenditures not exempt under the provisions of state or federal law, including:
The payee name;
The category or type of the expenditure;
A description of the reason for the expenditure, if available;
The expenditure amount; and
A link to the financial document, if the document is electronically available;
A searchable format;
Access to the current enacted Executive Branch Budget; and
A link to the public access Web site displays of the legislative and judicial branches of state government, and of the public institutions of higher education.
